CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 20, 1962, pg. A14 reads:"It's "Projection '62" - A distinguished panel of ten top-flight correspondents of the National Broadcasting Co. discuss foreign policy during a symposium sponsored by the Foreign Policy Association at the Hotel Hilton, last Thursday night.  Prior to the program, Frank McGee, left, moderator; Mrs. Brenda White, sercetary [secretary] to T.F. X. Higgins, executive director of the FPA, and Mr. Higgins, right, discuss final details of the meeting. -Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Frank McGee, Brenda White, and T.F. X. Higgins, posed in Hilton Hotel during Foreign Policy Association symposium
